{"id":18019,"title":"Making OP50 solution from Frozen Stock","title_html":"Making OP50 solution from Frozen Stock","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/default_protocol.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/default_protocol.png"},"doi":"dx.doi.org\/10.17504\/protocols.io.vube6sn","doi_status":2,"uri":"making-op50-solution-from-frozen-stock-vube6sn","type_id":1,"published_on":1542975985,"version_id":0,"created_on":1542975416,"categories":null,"creator":{"name":"Priota Islam","affiliation":"Imperial College London","username":"priota-islam","link":null,"image":{"source":"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/86b3npn.jpg","placeholder":"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/86b3npn.jpg"},"badges":[{"id":3,"image":{"source":"\/img\/badges\/silver.svg","placeholder":"\/img\/badges\/silver.svg"},"name":"Power author!"},{"id":6,"image":{"source":"\/img\/badges\/socialbutterfly.svg","placeholder":"\/img\/badges\/socialbutterfly.svg"},"name":"Social butterfly"}],"research_interests":null},"journal":null,"journal_name":null,"journal_link":null,"public":1,"has_versions":0,"link":null,"number_of_steps":4,"authors":[{"name":"Priota Islam","affiliation":"Imperial College London","username":"priota-islam","link":null,"image":{"source":"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/86b3npn.jpg","placeholder":"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/86b3npn.jpg"},"badges":[],"research_interests":null}],"versions":[],"groups":[{"id":850,"uri":"behavioural-genomics","title":"Behavioural Genomics","image":{"source":"","placeholder":"\/img\/group_placeholder.png"},"tech_support":{"email":null,"phone":null,"hide_contact":0,"use_email":0},"is_member":0,"request":{"id":850,"flag":0,"is_my":false,"uid":0,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"is_member":0}}],"has_subprotocols":0,"is_subprotocol":0,"is_bookmarked":0,"forks_count":{"private":0,"public":0},"steps":[{"id":685114,"guid":"56F95890EF1A11E8925597A5E53BE658","previous_id":null,"previous_guid":null,"modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"23420171C35848C0B296E0818242F4DA","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054723,"guid":"E2C556078728489A932D4FC025E6C154","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><h1>Day: 1<\/h1><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"> Get LB Agar from the media kitchen and autoclave it for 2hrs<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"> Post autoclave, pour the agar on large petri dishes (60mm) and leave to dry overnight to be transferred to the cold room the next day<\/li><\/ul><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF"},{"id":685115,"guid":"75C4A590EF1A11E8925597A5E53BE658","previous_id":685114,"previous_guid":"56F95890EF1A11E8925597A5E53BE658","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"AB897B98B8D74D0BBAC5ACA65569E45A","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054723,"guid":"3D0C7FAC53F14543A826F92199DDA543","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><h1>Day: 2<\/h1><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"> Get the frozen tube out of the freezer (Freezer 12, SD Box)<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"> Take a sterile pipette tip and get some frozen sample <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"> Streak the pipette on the LB agar plate<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"> Take another new pipette and streak across the old streak and then at a separate spot streak again<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"> Repeat this step for one more time<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"> Keep the plate at 37\u00b0C incubator overnight for the bacteria to grow<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"> Transfer the plate to the fridge the next day (This plate can be used for about 1 month to inoculate bacterial culture)<\/li><\/ul><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF"},{"id":685116,"guid":"7C0969E0EF1A11E8925597A5E53BE658","previous_id":685115,"previous_guid":"75C4A590EF1A11E8925597A5E53BE658","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"8588E96C09C8431FADD8D91CAF22B7BC","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054723,"guid":"851374CE85CD47148E9FA38ACCBC78AB","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><h1>Day:3 <\/h1><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"> Purchase LB Broth from the Media kitchen (Don\u2019t use less than 200ml)<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"> Get flat bottomed conical flasks from the glassware kitchen (For 200ml LB Broth take 400\/500ml flask to allow enough headspace for the bacteria)<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"> From the culture plate, select and circle a single colony <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"> Using aseptic technique, carefully scoop the single colony and mix it with the LB Broth that is already poured into the conical flask<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"> Label the flask and put it on the 37\u00b0C shaker for overnight incubation<\/li><\/ul><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF"},{"id":685117,"guid":"7F2E77A0EF1A11E8925597A5E53BE658","previous_id":685116,"previous_guid":"7C0969E0EF1A11E8925597A5E53BE658","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"A0E0AF39F0F24DE7BC6738F6D6E99117","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054723,"guid":"9D5544EC7C284F42A790FB781540F0A6","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><h1>Day:4 <\/h1><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"> Following overnight incubation, take the flask out of the incubator and measure the OD using a spectrophotometer<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"> Record the average of the OD600, use LB Broth as Blank<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"> Aliquot the solution into labelled 15ml falcon tubes and keep them in the 4\u00b0C Fridge<\/li><\/ul><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF"}],"materials":[],"description":null}